						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the Sōmēśvara temple. Fourth pillar Museum No. 84.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1109 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record is engraved at the end of No. 66 above. It states that Malli-seṭṭi son of Balli-seṭṭi made a gift of eight <hi rend="italic">gadyaṇās</hi> for a perpetual lamp to the god Svayambhu Sōmanātha of Kollipāka for the merit of Māyikabbe.</p>						

						<p>This undated record may be ascribed to the same date of the previous record [No. 66] 1109 A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
